# Dani-style Stuffed Chicken (PETTI DI POLLO DANI)

## Ingredients (Serves 6)
- 6 chicken breasts
- 2 tablespoons breadcrumbs
- 2 tablespoons Parmigiano cheese
- 1 clove garlic
- 1 tablespoon parsley
- 1/2 cup white wine
- Salt and pepper to taste
- Olive oil as needed

## Instructions

### 1. Preparation
- Mince the garlic and parsley
- Flatten chicken breasts by pounding with a wooden mallet

### 2. Make the Coating
- In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, cheese, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper, and olive oil

### 3. Prepare the Chicken
- Place coating mixture on one side of each chicken breast
- Fold in half
- Secure with toothpicks

### 4. Cooking
- Heat olive oil in a pan
- Add prepared chicken pieces
- Sprinkle remaining coating on top
- Cook both sides until well done
- Pour white wine along sides of pan
- Reduce until liquid is almost gone

*Note: This recipe can also be made with beef or pork.*
